entry.title: The Double Taxation Relief and International Tax Enforcement (Ethiopia) Order 2011

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Double Taxation Relief and International Tax Enforcement (Ethiopia) Order 2011

entry.summary: The Schedule to this Order contains an agreement and a protocol (“the Arrangements”) made between the Government of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland and the Government of the Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia for the avoidance of double taxation and prevention of fiscal evasion. This Order brings the Arrangements into effect.

entry.title: The Turks and Caicos Islands (Electoral District Boundary Commission) Order 2011
entry.summary: This Order provides for the establishment of an Electoral District Boundary Commission in the Turks and Caicos Islands, and for the Commission to make recommendations on the boundaries of ten electoral districts for the purpose of elections to the House of Assembly established by the Constitution set out in Schedule 2 to the Turks and Caicos Islands Constitution Order 2011. It also provides for the Governor of the Islands to enact legislation to give effect to the Commission’s recommendations, with or without modifications. These are necessary preparatory steps before the new Constitution can be brought into force and a general election held in the Islands.

entry.title: Act of Sederunt (Sanction for the Employment of Counsel in the Sheriff Court) 2011
entry.summary: General regulation 12 in the Schedule to the Act of Sederunt that makes provision about the fees of solicitors in the sheriff court (S.I. 1993/3080), provides that the fees of counsel or a solicitor advocate are allowable only where the court has granted sanction for the employment of counsel. This Act of Sederunt contains rules relating to the procedure for obtaining such sanction.

entry.title: The Double Taxation Relief and International Tax Enforcement (Hungary) Order 2011

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Double Taxation Relief and International Tax Enforcement (Hungary) Order 2011

entry.summary: The Schedule to this Order contains an agreement and a protocol (“the Arrangements”) made between the Government of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland and the Government of the Republic of Hungary for the avoidance of double taxation and prevention of fiscal evasion. This Order brings the Arrangements into effect.

entry.title: The Libya (Restrictive Measures) (Overseas Territories) (Amendment) Order 2011
entry.summary: The Order amends the Libya (Restrictive Measures) (Overseas Territories) Order 2011 to give effect to resolution 2009 (2011) adopted by the Security Council of the United Nations on 16th September 2011 and Council Regulation (EU) No 965/2011 adopted by the Council of the European Union on 28th September 2011. It also gives effect to a change to the humanitarian purposes exemption to the EU autonomous asset freeze, which was introduced by Council Regulation (EU) No. 572/2011 adopted by the Council of the European Union on 16th June 2011, amending Council Regulation (EU) No 204/2011. The Order also makes minor corrections to the principal Order.

entry.title: Act of Sederunt (Fees of Solicitors and Witnesses in the Sheriff Court) (Amendment) 2011
entry.summary: This Act of Sederunt makes amendments to the Act of Sederunt (Fees of Witnesses and Shorthand Writers in the Sheriff Court) 1992 (S.I. 1992/1878) and the Act of Sederunt (Fees of Solicitors in the Sheriff Court) (Amendment and Further Provisions) 1993 (S.I. 1993/3080).

entry.title: Act of Sederunt (Lands Valuation Appeal Court) 2011
entry.summary: This Act of Sederunt appoints the judges who may hear appeals under section 7 of the Valuation of Lands (Scotland) Amendment Act 1879. It revokes the Act of Sederunt (Lands Valuation Appeal Court) 2010, which previously made such provision.

entry.title: The NHS Bodies (Transfer of Trust Property) Order 2011
entry.summary: This Order transfers to the relevant new Trusts, property held on trust by the relevant old Trusts and makes related provision. Copies of the schedules of trust property transferred under this Order can be obtained from the Department of Health, Quarry House, Quarry Hill, Leeds LS2 7UE.

entry.title: The Central Rating List (England) (Amendment) Regulations 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Central Rating List (England) Regulations 2005 (“the Central Rating List Regulations”).

entry.title: The Planning (Fees) (Amendment No. 2) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Planning (Fees) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005 which prescribe fees payable to the Department of the Environment in respect of applications made under the Planning (Northern Ireland) Order 1991. The Regulations increase planning fees by approximately 2.9% overall.

entry.title: The Policing Protocol Order 2011
entry.summary: Section 79 of the Police Reform and Social Responsibility Act 2011 requires the Secretary of State to issue a Policing Protocol, namely a document setting out, or otherwise making provision about, the ways in which relevant persons should exercise or refrain from exercising functions so as to encourage, maintain or improve working relationships or limit or prevent the overlapping or conflicting exercise of functions. “Relevant persons” for these purposes are the Secretary of State (in the exercise of her policing functions), elected local policing bodies (namely police and crime commissioners and the Mayor’s Office for Policing and Crime), chief officers of police forces maintained by elected local policing bodies, and police and crime panels. These persons must have regard to the Policing Protocol in exercising their functions.

entry.title: The Al-Qaida (Asset-Freezing) Regulations 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations make provision relating to the enforcement of Council Regulation (EC) No. 881/2002 of 27 May 2002 (OJ No. L 139, 29.05.2002, p.9) imposing certain specific restrictive measures directed against certain persons and entities associated with the Al-Qaida network (“the Council Regulation”).

entry.title: The Cambridge City Fringes Joint Committee (Revocation) Order 2011
entry.summary: This Order revokes the Cambridge City Fringes Joint Committee Order 2009. That Order established a joint committee between Cambridgeshire County Council, Cambridge City Council and South Cambridgeshire District Council in respect of the area specified in the Agreement between those authorities dated 9 September 2008.

entry.title: The Infrastructure Planning (Environmental Impact Assessment) (Amendment) Regulations 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Infrastructure Planning (Environmental Impact Assessment) Regulations 2009 (the “2009 Regulations”) S.I. 2009/2263. The 2009 Regulations implemented, in relation to nationally significant infrastructure projects, Council Directive 85/337/EEC on the assessment of the effects of certain public and private projects on the environment (O.J. No L 175, 5.7.19985, p. 40), as amended by Council Directive 97/11/EC (O.J. No. L 73, 14.3.1997, p. 5).

entry.title: The Licensing and Regulation of Taxis (Appeals in Respect of Taxi Fares) (Scotland) Amendment Order 2011
entry.summary: This Order amends the Licensing and Regulation of Taxis (Appeals in Respect of Taxi Fares) (Scotland) Order 1985 (“the 1985 Order”) in consequence of changes made to section 18 of the Civic Government (Scotland) Act 1982 by section 174(4) of the Criminal Justice and Licensing (Scotland) Act 2010 (asp 13). The 1985 Order is amended so as to reflect that appeals under section 18 can now also be brought by any person or organisation appearing to the traffic commissioner to be representative of taxi operators in a relevant area.

entry.title: The Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 (Exemption) (Amendment No. 2) Order 2011

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 (Exemption) (Amendment No. 2) Order 2011

entry.summary: This Order amends the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 (Exemption) Order 2001 (S.I. 2001/1201) (“the Exemption Order”).

entry.title: The Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) (Amendment) Regulations 2011

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) (Amendment) Regulations 2011

entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) Regulations 2010 (“the 2010 Regulations”).

entry.title: The Children and Young Persons Act 2008 (Commencement No.4) (England) Order 2011
entry.summary: This Order is the fourth Commencement Order made by the Secretary of State under the Children and Young Persons Act 2008 (“the Act”) which brings provisions of the Act into force only in relation to England.

entry.title: The Fodder Plant Seeds (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Fodder Plant Seeds Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2009 (“the principal Regulations”) in order to implement Commission Directive 2010/60 (O.J. L228, 31.8.2010) (“the Directive”). Commission Directive 2010/60/EC provides for certain derogations for marketing of fodder plant seed mixtures intended for use in the preservation of the natural environment.
